FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q: Can I use this for a commercial project?
A: Yes, the MIT License allows commercial use without restriction.

Q: Do I need to credit the original author?
A: Yes, you must include the copyright notice and license text when
   distributing the software.

Q: Can I modify the code without asking permission?
A: Yes, you can modify the code freely. No permission is required.

Q: Can I include this in proprietary software?
A: Yes, MIT-licensed code can be included in proprietary projects.

Q: Do I need to open-source my modifications?
A: No, unlike some licenses, MIT does not require you to share your
   modifications publicly.

Q: Can I change the license for my modified version?
A: You can add additional terms to your modifications, but you must
   still include the original MIT License notice.

Q: Is there any warranty or support?
A: No, the software is provided "as is" with no warranty or support
   obligations from the authors.

Q: Can I remove the license from my copy?
A: No, the license and copyright notices must be included in all copies
   or substantial portions of the software.

